[
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Elihu also proceeded, and said,",
    "hash": "73dc2ab60b650aa9288c7d72d715985eb4f7c53dc1a38b5fcea149bbe78eb660"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Suffer me a little, and I will shew thee that {I have} yet to speak on God's behalf. {I have...: Heb. there are yet words for God}",
    "hash": "8928afdb6149f6a9e17a95d928ec57d1300870d27fc9ed276495d73362802cfa"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "I will fetch my knowledge from afar, and will ascribe righteousness to my Maker.",
    "hash": "1fe01752f43ceeed054827c371230850fe808385a2c7b7c7a325d824e725e776"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For truly my words {shall} not {be} false: he that is perfect in knowledge {is} with thee.",
    "hash": "bf539c04825a0c4f6b73126fe40cbd7a3b2163e350404be509aa0cf328d6b956"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Behold, God {is} mighty, and despiseth not {any: he is} mighty in strength {and} wisdom. {wisdom: Heb. heart}",
    "hash": "7324b43c67ce65cedf328f24e20c4500ee127b4ef5a1934cb0dc59a97310cc5a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "He preserveth not the life of the wicked: but giveth right to the poor. {poor: or, afflicted}",
    "hash": "2874c2098a46fca199f8a3916b1b4c124e927653e996e89fa927d269bccfbc62"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "He withdraweth not his eyes from the righteous: but with kings {are they} on the throne; yea, he doth establish them for ever, and they are exalted.",
    "hash": "a9e947eb94d5d9de278546d78d646625bc1ac450a99e553fd7e8e36f9547f1e2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And if {they be} bound in fetters, {and} be holden in cords of affliction;",
    "hash": "de1280c239b2b89dab3b9870dceaf513370b8de0900f23c4503401c95140c043"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Then he sheweth them their work, and their transgressions that they have exceeded.",
    "hash": "465bddcd6f59511c7d7134df3f3a29266a0108721a70daa5b79a925212f4a403"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "He openeth also their ear to discipline, and commandeth that they return from iniquity.",
    "hash": "aa66fabc92d6ae40d9faefcd40ada0dc0907ee892b0d21793929ff666b89f848"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "If they obey and serve {him}, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.",
    "hash": "9960ad288254aa2962cc6fb0cdb558958f4da2656f094bd0c11d373927aecc58"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "But if they obey not, they shall perish by the sword, and they shall die without knowledge. {perish: Heb. pass away}",
    "hash": "4c13ab0220902eb63564110fc899ef58e8877641d51ed01b220873791fb3c1f6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But the hypocrites in heart heap up wrath: they cry not when he bindeth them.",
    "hash": "7eb1d4260572e1729763bc8072f4e89551054233443f84a7681b2f8c3583f5f5"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "They die in youth, and their life {is} among the unclean. {They...: Heb. Their soul dieth} {unclean: or, sodomites}",
    "hash": "2785a529d8cece94e1e753a22044b5a2b78672c89027ddb943132ccb90ed6ace"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "He delivereth the poor in his affliction, and openeth their ears in oppression. {poor: or, afflicted}",
    "hash": "e669ba500181384e7c5ea8cfe5712d600c29aec7256476fbb69bd0e9ee076576"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Even so would he have removed thee out of the strait {into} a broad place, where {there is} no straitness; and that which should be set on thy table {should be} full of fatness. {that...: Heb. the rest of thy table}",
    "hash": "49ac1c8f72eda949cc24d918c26afab102e126d73379822386909d113f183a08"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But thou hast fulfilled the judgment of the wicked: judgment and justice take hold {on thee}. {take...: or, should uphold thee}",
    "hash": "e39d46e8c62676951506dc432b391069e973458b7ff2458b59632196e4e0ae13"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Because {there is} wrath, {beware} lest he take thee away with {his} stroke: then a great ransom cannot deliver thee. {deliver...: Heb. turn thee aside}",
    "hash": "b6b9c94d77b6208b5d88febbc2fdfb8f292cc9ac6dbf1b430ee552b53dd5f665"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Will he esteem thy riches? {no}, not gold, nor all the forces of strength.",
    "hash": "728fec62c9b6f57e4ecab21718eee9a46e3ec10d98955df2a2e7401b99d5dfe8"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Desire not the night, when people are cut off in their place.",
    "hash": "78b65cb3c246396e03f2cfaa31ac71924877a4fe28dbafe7af9c0d6edd20015f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Take heed, regard not iniquity: for this hast thou chosen rather than affliction.",
    "hash": "c2e9e30786194b31ae979ccd9179f372156e521269f4727ed27999754b36cf23"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Behold, God exalteth by his power: who teacheth like him?",
    "hash": "223e2a9c6005c59b49db4bfa1a4e7d461111cdf842284495f4b7cf02db05ad4a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Who hath enjoined him his way? or who can say, Thou hast wrought iniquity?",
    "hash": "ea8debf74d149c4143d10202d35ac806419f2daaf33dbcfb758cf8d0b297b2c0"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Remember that thou magnify his work, which men behold.",
    "hash": "b027d1c9a7089979464bacbc10526a1c9529eb3c9129985776cb4de696e78631"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Every man may see it; man may behold {it} afar off.",
    "hash": "8e8e27102d54522fd73c4012ff7313c729a53dc48067eaccb9df330505cf1a06"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Behold, God {is} great, and we know {him} not, neither can the number of his years be searched out.",
    "hash": "35ca059964f90eb9e1923a4c372dd0128141a9c12284341de4d7f3988487b395"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For he maketh small the drops of water: they pour down rain according to the vapour thereof:",
    "hash": "39ba4cfabddf9d440ddcf53675f900b625d7587dc409a99596e9fb66f2a8b2a3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Which the clouds do drop {and} distil upon man abundantly.",
    "hash": "1168995c2cabcb9ea2e4dbb1a8686a406d43120734478db0eb597f13156d701f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Also can {any} understand the spreadings of the clouds, {or} the noise of his tabernacle?",
    "hash": "9f0750c18cf17a5182f8a964347408cf7ffbc921dda8c6caff91f90b51f926dc"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Behold, he spreadeth his light upon it, and covereth the bottom of the sea. {bottom: Heb. roots}",
    "hash": "a0a1ac3112eae06bbcc3366256509ea7a69635d82cce175f9dbdd7df21433ea4"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.31",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "For by them judgeth he the people; he giveth meat in abundance.",
    "hash": "4f9c331819e0a62dfba3b6166d976cf1f69e2b39a48069a1b3c77eb1f195c773"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.32",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "With clouds he covereth the light; and commandeth it {not to shine} by {the cloud} that cometh betwixt.",
    "hash": "4e771a75ccaa89da8c4186308083a8637c77ee03d8c86f0fe5240cae5953cf6d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.36.33",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 36,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "The noise thereof sheweth concerning it, the cattle also concerning the vapour. {the vapour: Heb. that which goeth up}",
    "hash": "4efbe6bb0c31b45d9ddafb2d6f9db624307a0cce34e397bba7bc9bb136ae9477"
  }
]